I say you'd need a dedicated rooter or two (or just have a mage pet) - hell, make a druid feel like the most important member of a raid for once *smirk Dind*.  It'll fix aggro issues since rooted mobs attack the thing closest to them - the main tank can just position herself to be the closest thing to the mob.<br>
<br>
We are at a place now where I think we can easily take at least two or three at a time (Gab, Got, Vig) with little sweat and we do have the backup melee to cover a bad situation.<br>
<br>
Shouldn't try this in Umbral, which has funky agro issues; and should definitely not try this in Cazic, where taunt is broken. I'm thinking .... Arena, Seb, Chardok .... we could have one helluva CB raid.<br>
